                            <comment id="54371" author="utopiabound" created="Tue, 19 Mar 2013 14:38:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/5767&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/5767&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Make 8b slow until &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2887&quot; title=&quot;sanity-quota test_12a: slow due to ZFS VMs sharing single disk&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-2887&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-2887&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is addressed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="54369" author="utopiabound" created="Tue, 19 Mar 2013 14:34:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This test fails A LOT, but looking at the results, it appears to run variably between 1500s and 7600s (some passed results are well above normal 3600 timeout).  I would say this is another instance of slow zfs sync behaviour (&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2887&quot; title=&quot;sanity-quota test_12a: slow due to ZFS VMs sharing single disk&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-2887&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-2887&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
